\title{Modal maps}
\author{samueltoth}
\date{2025-05-10}
\taxon{Module}

\import{stt-macros}


% ```agda
\agda{
module Modalities.ModalMaps  where

open import Foundations.Prelude
open import Modalities.Subuniverses
}
% ```

\subtree[stt-0045]{
\taxon{Definition}

\p{Given a [subuniverse](stt-003Z) #{S}, we say that a map of
functions is in #{S} when all it's fibres are in #{S}.}

% ```agda
\agda{
is-modal-map : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥 𝓜} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥}
                 (S : SubU (𝓤 ⊔ 𝓥) 𝓜)
               → (A → B) → Type _
is-modal-map S f = ∀ b → fibre f b ∈ S
}
% ```

\p{
Likewise, if #{S} is in addition a [reflective subuniverse](stt-0041) a map is
#{S}-connected when all of its fibres are.
}

% ```agda
\agda{
is-connected-map : ∀ {𝓤 𝓥 𝓜} {A : Type 𝓤} {B : Type 𝓥}
                     {S : SubU (𝓤 ⊔ 𝓥) 𝓜}
                   → is-reflective S
                   → (A → B) → Type (𝓤 ⊔ 𝓥)
is-connected-map rfl f = ∀ b → is-connected rfl (fibre f b)
}
% ```
}
